<a name="part-3"></a>
# PART 3 — LESSON SYSTEM DESIGN

## A. Every Lesson Must Have These Fields

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| `id` | Integer | Unique identifier in DB |
| `subject_id` | Integer (FK) | Connects lesson to its subject |
| `title` | String | The display name of the lesson |
| `subtitle` | String | A short description / teaser for the lesson |
| `lesson_order` | Integer | The sequential position (1–10) |
| `difficulty` | Enum: easy/medium/hard | Visual difficulty indicator |
| `status` | Computed: done/active/locked | Derived per student — not stored in lessons table |
| `video_url` | URL String | Embedded YouTube / video link |
| `video_title` | String | Descriptive title of the video content |
| `duration_minutes` | Integer | Expected time to complete |
| `quiz_questions` | Array (from questions table) | 3 questions: MCQ + fill_blank + true_false |
| `games` | Array (from games table) | Optional bonus games |
| `created_at` | Timestamp | Audit trail |

> **Note:** `status` is **never stored** in the lessons table. It is **computed at runtime** by comparing the student's progress records against the lesson's `lesson_order`. This keeps the lessons table clean and reusable across all students.

---

## B. The Purpose of Each Key Field

- **`lesson_order`** — this IS the curriculum sequence. Every unlock decision is based on comparing a student's highest completed `lesson_order` vs. the current lesson's order.
- **`video_url`** — the primary learning delivery mechanism. The student watches before attempting the quiz.
- **`status` (computed)** — this drives the entire visual state of the lesson card (locked gray, active glowing, done green checkmark).
- **`quiz_questions`** — these are the assessment. Without them, there's no measurable learning.
- **`difficulty`** — this helps set student expectations. A student who sees "Hard" prepares themselves mentally.

---

## C. What Makes One Lesson Feel Complete

A lesson is **complete** when a student has:
1. ✅ Watched the video (or scrolled past the video player)  
2. ✅ Answered all 3 quiz questions  
3. ✅ Submitted their answers  
4. ✅ Received a score (even 0/3 — completion is not perfection)

A lesson feeling **pedagogically complete** means:
- The video introduces the concept clearly
- The MCQ tests recognition
- The Fill-in-the-Blank tests recall
- The True/False tests comprehension
- Together, these 3 question types cover 3 different cognitive levels

---

## D. Visual and Logical Structure of a Lesson

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  LESSON HEADER                                  │
│  Title: "Multiplication Tables (2–5)"           │
│  Subject: Mathematics · Grade 4 · Lesson 4      │
│  Difficulty: ⭐⭐ Medium                         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  VIDEO SECTION                                  │
│  [Embedded YouTube Player]                      │
│  Video Title: "Learn Times Tables 2 to 5"       │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  QUIZ SECTION                                   │
│  Question 1: MCQ (4 options)                   │
│  Question 2: Fill in the Blank                 │
│  Question 3: True / False                      │
│  [SUBMIT ANSWERS Button]                        │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  BONUS GAME (optional)                          │
│  [Play Times Table Blaster 🎮]                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

