<a name="part-13"></a>
# PART 13 — FINAL PRODUCT RULES

## 🏛️ FUNNOVA CORE LOGIC SYSTEM

These are the permanent, non-negotiable rules of the FUNNOVA platform.

---

### 📚 CURRICULUM RULES

```
RULE C-1: The platform supports exactly 2 grades: Grade 4 and Grade 5.
RULE C-2: Each grade has exactly 2 subjects: Mathematics and Science.
RULE C-3: Each subject has exactly 10 lessons.
RULE C-4: Lessons are arranged in order: Easy (1–3) → Medium (4–7) → Hard (8–10).
RULE C-5: A student only ever sees content for their own registered grade.
RULE C-6: Lesson order is permanent and cannot be skipped.
```

---

### 📝 LESSON RULES

```
RULE L-1: Every lesson must have: title, lesson_order, video_url.
RULE L-2: Every lesson must have exactly 3 questions: 1 MCQ + 1 Fill_Blank + 1 True_False.
RULE L-3: Lesson status (done/active/locked) is COMPUTED per student — never stored in the lessons table.
RULE L-4: A lesson has exactly 1 active state at a time per student per subject.
RULE L-5: The first lesson of any subject is always "active" for a new student.
```

---

### ❓ QUESTION RULES

```
RULE Q-1: Every lesson has exactly 3 questions. No more. No less.
RULE Q-2: Question types must be: MCQ (order 1), Fill_Blank (order 2), True_False (order 3).
RULE Q-3: Each question is worth exactly 1 point.
RULE Q-4: Maximum score per lesson = 3.
RULE Q-5: Correct answer comparison is case-insensitive and whitespace-trimmed.
RULE Q-6: MCQ correct_answer stores the option letter (A, B, C, or D).
RULE Q-7: Fill_Blank and True_False correct_answer stores the full expected answer string.
```

---

### 📊 SCORE RULES

```
RULE S-1: Score per lesson is 0–3 (one point per correct answer).
RULE S-2: Subject score is cumulative: SUM of all lesson scores for completed lessons.
RULE S-3: Score feedback has 4 tiers: 3/3 (Perfect), 2/3 (Great), 1/3 (Keep Going), 0/3 (Don't Give Up).
RULE S-4: Score popup always shows: emoji + title + message + per-question result.
RULE S-5: Score is stored at two levels: question-level (student_progress) and subject-level (student_scores).
RULE S-6: A submitted score can NEVER be altered by re-submission (UNIQUE constraint enforces this).
```

---

### 🔓 UNLOCK RULES

```
RULE U-1: A lesson becomes "done" ONLY after quiz submission — not when the video is watched.
RULE U-2: The next lesson unlocks immediately after the current lesson's quiz is submitted.
RULE U-3: A student does NOT need a passing score to unlock the next lesson.
RULE U-4: Unlock logic is enforced server-side. The client cannot self-report lesson completion.
RULE U-5: The UNIQUE(student_id, question_id) constraint prevents a student from submitting the same question twice.
```

---

### 📈 PROGRESS RULES

```
RULE P-1: A lesson is "completed" when all 3 of its questions have a student_progress row for the student.
RULE P-2: Subject progress percentage = (completed_lessons / 10) × 100.
RULE P-3: Overall progress = (total_completed_across_all_subjects / total_lessons_in_grade) × 100.
RULE P-4: Dashboard data is always computed fresh from the database — never cached on the client.
RULE P-5: Progress bars visually represent lesson-based completion percentage, not score percentage.
RULE P-6: Score percentage (accuracy) and progress percentage (completion) are shown separately.
```

---

### 🔒 SECURITY RULES

```
RULE SEC-1: All protected endpoints require a valid JWT in the Authorization header.
RULE SEC-2: student_id in JWT must match the student_id in the request body for progress APIs.
RULE SEC-3: Admin endpoints require role = 'admin' in JWT.
RULE SEC-4: Passwords are always stored as bcrypt hashes — never plaintext.
RULE SEC-5: The lessons/status endpoint always re-derives status from the database, never trusting client input.
```

---

### 🎨 EXPERIENCE RULES

```
RULE UX-1: Locked lessons are visually distinct (gray, lock icon). Active lessons are visually prominent (glow/color).
RULE UX-2: The Submit button is disabled until all 3 questions are answered.
RULE UX-3: Score popup appears immediately after submission — no navigation delay.
RULE UX-4: The score popup always offers exactly 2 actions: [Next Lesson] and [Back to Lessons].
RULE UX-5: Progress bars must update immediately after quiz submission — no refresh required.
RULE UX-6: New students always see a warm welcome with their name, grade, and avatar on the dashboard.
```

---

> **This document is the Single Source of Truth for FUNNOVA v1.**  
> Every development decision — frontend layout, backend query, database schema change — must be validated against these rules.  
> When in doubt, refer back to the rule that governs it.

---

*FUNNOVA Product Blueprint · Version 1.0 · April 2026*  
*Designed for Grade 4–5 students · Mathematics & Science · 10 Lessons per Subject*
